      • data

        public static DataFactory data​(Decorator decorator,
                               Charset charset,
                               Path... files)
        Creates a DataFactory where data exists in multiple files. If the first line of the first file is a header, E.g. defaultFormatNodeFileHeader() can be used to extract that.
        Parameters:
        decorator - Decorator for this data.
        charset - Charset to read data in.
        files - the files making up the data.
        Returns:
        DataFactory that returns a CharSeeker over all the supplied files.

      • data

        public static DataFactory data​(Decorator decorator,
                               Supplier<CharReadable> readable)
        Parameters:
        decorator - Decorator for this data.
        readable - we need to have this as a Factory since one data file may be opened and scanned multiple times.
        Returns:
        DataFactory that returns a CharSeeker over the supplied readable

      • defaultFormatNodeFileHeader

        public static Header.Factory defaultFormatNodeFileHeader​(Supplier<ZoneId> defaultTimeZone,
                                                         boolean normalizeTypes)
        Header parser that will read header information, using the default node header format, from the top of the data file. This header factory can be used even when the header exists in a separate file, if that file is the first in the list of files supplied to data(org.neo4j.internal.batchimport.input.csv.Decorator, java.nio.charset.Charset, java.nio.file.Path...).
        Parameters:
        defaultTimeZone - A supplier of the time zone to be used for temporal values when not specified explicitly
        normalizeTypes - whether or not to normalize types.
